abilities.name: Damage Swap
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokemon to another as long as you don't Knock Out that Pokemon. This power can't be used if Alakazam is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

abilities.name: Rain Dance
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach 1 Water Energy card to 1 of your Water Pokemon. (This doesn't use up your 1 Energy card attachment for the turn.) This power can't be used if Blastoise is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. Extra Water Energy after the 2nd doesn't count.

attacks.name: Scrunch

attacks.name: Double-edge
attacks.text: Chansey does 80 damage to itself.

abilities.name: Energy Burn
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all Energy attached to Charizard into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fire Spin

attacks.name: Metronome

attacks.name: Bubblebeam

abilities.name: Strikes Back

name: Clefairy Doll
rules: Play Clefairy Doll as if it were a Basic Pokemon. While in play, Clefairy Doll counts a a Pokemon (instead of a Trainer card). Clefairy Doll has no attacks, can't retreat, and can't be Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned. If Clefairy Doll is Knocked Out, it doesn't count as a Knocked Out Pokemon. At any time during your turn before your attack, you may discard Clefairy Doll.

name: Computer Search
rules: Discard 2 of the other cards from your hand in order to search your deck for any card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Devolution Spray
rules: Choose 1 of your own Pokemon in play and a Stage of Evolution. Discard all Evolution cards of that Stage or higher attached to that Pokemon. That Pokemon is no longer Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, Poisoned, or anything else that might be the result of an attack (just as if you had evolved it).

name: Impostor Professor Oak
rules: Your opponent shuffles his or her hand into his or her deck, then draws 7 cards.

name: Item Finder
rules: Discard 2 of the other cards from your hand in order to put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Lass
rules: You and your opponent show each other your hands, then shuffle all the Trainer cards from your hands into your decks.

name: Pokemon Breeder
rules: Put a Stage 2 Evolution card from your hand on the matching Basic Pokemon. You can only play this card when you would be allowed to evolve that Pokemon anyway.

name: Pokemon Trader
rules: Trade 1 of the Basic Pokemon or Evolution cards in your hand for 1 of the Basic Pokemon or Evolution cards from your deck. Show both cards to your opponent. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Scoop Up
rules: Choose 1 of your Pokemon in play and return its Basic Pokemon card to your hand. (Discard all cards attached to that card.)

name: Super Energy Removal
rules: Discard 1 Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokemon in order to choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and up to 2 Energy cards attached to it. Discard those Energy cards.

name: Defender
rules: Attach Defender to 1 of your Pokemon. At the end of your opponent's next turn, discard Defender. Damage done to that Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Energy Retrieval
rules: Trade 1 of the other cards in your hand for up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile.

name: Full Heal
rules: Your Active Pokemon is no longer Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned.

name: Maintenance
rules: Shuffle 2 of the other cards from your hand into your deck in order to draw a card.

name: PlusPower
rules: Attach PlusPower to your Active Pokemon. At the end of your turn, discard PlusPower. If this Pokemon's attack does damage to the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the attack does 10 more damage to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Pokemon Center
rules: Remove all damage counters from all of your own Pokemon with damage counters on them, then discard all Energy cards attached to those Pokemon.

name: Pokemon Flute
rules: Choose 1 Basic Pokemon card from your opponent's discard pile and put it onto his or her Bench. (You can't play Pokemon Flute if your opponent's Bench is full.)

name: Pokedex
rules: Look at up to 5 cards from the top of your deck and rearrange them as you like.

name: Professor Oak
rules: Discard your hand, then draw 7 cards.

name: Revive
rules: Put 1 Basic Pokemon card from your discard pile onto your Bench. Put damage counters on that Pokemon equal to half its HP (rounded down to the nearest 10). (You can't play Revive if your Bench is full.)

name: Super Potion
rules: Discard 1 Energy card attached to your own Pokemon in order to remove up to 4 damage counters from that Pokemon.

name: Bill
rules: Draw 2 cards.

name: Energy Removal
rules: Choose 1 Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and discard it.

name: Gust of Wind
rules: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and switch it with his or her Active Pokemon.

name: Potion
rules: Remove up to 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Switch
rules: Switch 1 of your own Benched Pokemon with your Active Pokemon.

name: Double Colorless Energy
rules: Provides ColorlessColorless energy. Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.
